{
  "stem": "2581.7",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "All of a sudden, she said to me, don't call me Greenovna, my name is Green, you know?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were many like-- many people like that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But-- but in a way, we lived with them in a relative-- I wouldn't say peace, but it was an accustomed way.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We knew how the relations that we had with them, but everything changed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "First, then they took away our radios, whoever had a radio.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they came to the houses and took what they wanted.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then in 1940, we were all transferred into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a small town.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They took part of the older part, you know?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was guarded by Jewish police, and-- which some of them weren't better than the Germans, you know?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they put fear in our hearts in different ways.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Like, we organized-- there was an organized, or appointed rather, leadership of the ghetto, the [NON-ENGLISH], or Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "No, I think they called them Judenrat, where a man by the name of Cochran was the leader.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this-- this committee had to prepare people to go to work, to send to work to the-- to the Germans.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, when people came back to the ghetto they would bring-- some would bring some potatoes, some bread, or some coal.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they wanted to stop that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they found on two Jewish boys, that happened to be immigrants from another town, you know?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "From this town, it would have been too much.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they-- they picked those two Jewish boys.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They found on them potatoes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They took the entire town out on a field outside of town to-- you have to watch the way these two boys were hung.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And you know, at that time, I was 14 years old.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
